%[text] # Modernizing a 2003 MATLAB GUI with Claude Code
%[text] *From GUIDE to App Designer in five prompts*
%%
%[text] ## The Starting Point
%[text] **Time Series Viewer** — a GUIDE-based app published on MATLAB File Exchange, originally written around 2003. It lets you interactively explore flight test time series data.
%[text:table]
%[text] | Metric | Original App |
%[text] | --- | --- |
%[text] | Framework | GUIDE (gui\_mainfcn + .fig binary) |
%[text] | Lines of code | ~3,255 across 16 files |
%[text] | OOP style | @class folders (pre-classdef) |
%[text] | Data source | evalin('base',...) workspace access |
%[text] | State management | setappdata / getappdata |
%[text] | Callbacks | String expressions ('datalabel down') |
%[text:table]
%[text] 
%[text] 
%[text] ![](text:image:03e8)
%%
%[text] ## The Result
%[text] A modern programmatic App Designer app with timetable-based data, file loading, and built-in axes toolbars.
%[text:table]
%[text] | Metric | Modernized App |
%[text] | --- | --- |
%[text] | Framework | uifigure + uigridlayout (programmatic) |
%[text] | Lines of code | 1,167 across 4 new files |
%[text] | OOP style | handle class (classdef) |
%[text] | Data source | File-based (.mat / .csv) loading |
%[text] | State management | App properties |
%[text] | Callbacks | Function handles @(~,~) app.method() |
%[text:table]
%[text] 
%[text] ![](text:image:9589)
%[text] 
%%
%[text] ## Setting up the Toolkit
%[text] Following the directions on the readme to setup the toolkit. The machine was not already configured with the MATLAB MCP Server.
%[text] ### Step 1:Clone the Toolkit Repo
%[text] ```
%[text] git clone https://github.com/matlab/matlab-agentic-toolkit.git
%[text] cd matlab-agentic-toolkit
%[text] ```
%[text] ### Step 2: Ask Claude to setup the toolkit
%[text] ```
%[text] claude
%[text] > Set up the toolkit
%[text] ```
%%
%[text] ## What I Typed — Five Prompts, Total
%[text] Here is every prompt I sent to Claude Code to produce the modernized app. The initial plan was developed interactively, then these prompts drove all code generation:
%%
%[text] ### Prompt 1: The Modernization Plan
%[text] **I wrote this app in the early 2000s. Let's update it, then make it awesome. First attempt- Use /code-modernization and /app-designer skills to convert to a modern code base. Use /testing to generate at least basic tests (don't worry about UI tests for now) to ensure that anything that works in the old app works in the new app. Generate some good synthetic test data that we can use for trying it out`**
%[text] This produced the initial `src/TimeSeriesViewer.m` (main app class), `src/generateSampleData.m` (synthetic data), and both test files. Claude ran all tests (16/16 passing) and launched the app to verify the disabled-on-startup UX.
%%
%[text] ### Prompt 2: Switch to Timetables
%[text] **`Update to use timetables instead of struct of struct. This may take a little thinking, since timetable couples time with variables. I think we should support multiple timetables, but then the user shouldn't have a choice of time — it's defined by the time variable of the table containing each variable`****.**
%[text] This refactored the entire data model:
%[text] - `struct` of `struct(.time, .values)` became a cell array of `timetable`s
%[text] - Time variables (`t`, `t2`) disappeared from the UI — time is intrinsic to each timetable
%[text] - Added `vectorsToTimetables()` for loading legacy flat `.mat` files
%[text] - Tests updated and expanded (20/20 passing) \
%%
%[text] ### Prompt 3: Clean Up Variable List
%[text] **`Remove length annotations from variable list. They aren't needed since variables carry their knowledge of time.`**
%[text] Removed the `"altitude  (10001)"` display format. Variables now show as plain names. Deleted `addLengthToParms`, `removeLengthFromParms`, and `getVariableLengths` — no longer needed.
%%
%[text] ### Prompt 4: Use Axes Toolbars
%[text] **`Replace the zoom and datatips button with the axes toolbar. Use axtoolbar`**
%[text] Replaced two custom toggle buttons and ~60 lines of manual zoom/datacursor state management with a single line per axis:
axtoolbar_example = "axtoolbar(ax, {'datacursor','pan','zoomin','zoomout','restoreview'})";
disp(axtoolbar_example)
%%
%[text] ### Prompt 5: Generate Sample Data Files
%[text] **`Generate a bunch of sample files that can be loaded into the app. Recommend where we should put them.`**
%[text] Claude recommended a `samples/` directory and created 7 files covering different domains and loading paths:
%[text:table]
%[text] | File | Domain | Format |
%[text] | --- | --- | --- |
%[text] | flight\_test.mat | Flight test (2 rates) | timetable |
%[text] | vehicle\_dynamics.mat | Automotive (200 Hz) | timetable |
%[text] | vibration\_analysis.mat | Bearing defect (2048 Hz) | timetable |
%[text] | multi\_rate\_sensors.mat | Drone: GPS+IMU+baro (3 rates) | timetable |
%[text] | power\_grid\_legacy.mat | Power grid | flat vectors (legacy) |
%[text] | weather\_station.csv | Weather (1 week) | CSV |
%[text] | biomedical\_signals.csv | ECG + respiration (500 Hz) | CSV |
%[text:table]
%%
%[text] ## Deprecated Patterns Eliminated
%[text:table]
%[text] | Old Pattern | Modern Replacement |
%[text] | --- | --- |
%[text] | `gui\_mainfcn` + `.fig` binary | `uifigure` + `uigridlayout` class |
%[text] | `evalin('base',...)` | `app.DataTables` + file-based loading |
%[text] | `@dragndrop` class folder | Multi-select dropdowns per axis |
%[text] | `setappdata` / `getappdata` | App properties |
%[text] | `guidata(hObject, handles)` | `app.PropertyName` |
%[text] | `isstr` | `ischar` / `isstring` |
%[text] | `str2num` | `str2double` |
%[text] | `strmatch` | `startsWith` / `matches` |
%[text] | `lasterr` | `catch e` with `e.message` |
%[text] | String callbacks | Function handle callbacks |
%[text] | `gco` / `gcf` / `gca` | Explicit handle references |
%[text] | Custom zoom/datatip toggles | `axtoolbar` |
%[text] | Struct-of-structs data | `timetable` (one per sample rate) |
%[text:table]
%%
%[text] ## File Structure
%[text] Old files are untouched — the original app remains runnable. All new code is in `src/`, `tests/`, and `samples/`.
dir_output = ["src/"
    "  TimeSeriesViewer.m        — Main app class (626 lines)"
    "  generateSampleData.m      — Synthetic data generator (88 lines)"
    "tests/"
    "  TimeSeriesViewerTest.m    — 8 unit tests for data logic"
    "  generateSampleDataTest.m  — 9 unit tests for sample data"
    "samples/"
    "  generateAllSamples.m      — Regeneration script"
    "  flight_test.mat            vehicle_dynamics.mat"
    "  vibration_analysis.mat     multi_rate_sensors.mat"
    "  power_grid_legacy.mat      weather_station.csv"
    "  biomedical_signals.csv"];
disp(char(dir_output))
%%
%[text] ## Live Demo: Launch the App
addpath('src');
TimeSeriesViewer;
%%
%[text] ## Results
%[text] Using the toolkit, five natural-language prompts produced a complete modernization:
%[text] - **626-line** App class replacing a 3,255-line GUIDE app
%[text] - **Timetable-native** data model with multi-rate support
%[text] - **17 unit tests** all passing
%[text] - **7 sample data files** across multiple domains and formats
%[text] - **Zero deprecated function warnings** from Code Analyzer \

